            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do agencies handle client handoff with AI builders?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Three models: (1) Retain ownership with maintenance fee, (2) Transfer ownership to client, (3) Code export from Webflow/Framer. Choose based on client type and revenue goals."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can agencies really scale with AI website builders?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes, but plan for bottlenecks. Team collaboration limits: Framer 3 editors, Webflow 2-3, Wix Studio unlimited. Scale comes from process: standardize templates, create reusable components, batch similar projects."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What's the ROI for agencies switching to AI builders?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Calculate: Old hourly rate √ó Hours saved √ó Projects per month. Example: $150/hr √ó 12 hours saved √ó 10 projects = $18,000/month additional capacity. Options: increase margins, competitive pricing, or scale output."
            }
          }
        ]
      }}
    />
    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">Agencies have excellent AI options. Webflow for complex projects, Framer for design, Durable for speed.</p>
      <a href="/guides" class="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block">
        View All Guides ‚Üí
      </a>
